5:
So, um... Mary. All I have to do is put
this on?
10: Y-yeah! And you'll be glad you did!
21:
We've got him! The target's heart
rate is rising. It's working!
24:
Heh, off to a strong start. Maintain
momentum and strike when the
time is right!
33:
This is amazing, right? My friend lent
me those things we just put on. They
can bring us to a place like this
instantly and without any magic!
37:
Ah... Yeah. I was just thinking about
how you've wanted to see the ocean
for so long.
40:
So I'm glad you finally could. I don't
think I can thank your friend enough
for this!
44:
Yeah... It's true that I've wanted to
see the ocean for a while, but...
47:
I... wanted to see it with you. I
wanted to walk on the beach
together, so...
51:
So, uh! We're here now, so let's make
the most of it!
57:
C'mon, boy! Make your move!
Maybe we should play with the
settings a bit, huh? Turn up the heat
a little!
61:
You idiot, it's fine as is!
Come on, Mary! Now's your chance!
Reel him in!
69: M-Mary, no! We'll catch a cold!
73:
Don't worry, Will! This is a virtual
space, so we're not actually getting
wet!
76:
Hehe, this is just like a dream!
Together on the beach like this...
79:
Maybe we'll be able to see the
ocean for real someday. And then...
Maybe I'll be able to find my Float—
82:
N-never mind, it's nothing!
Anyway, let's go swimming!
90:
I'll do everything I can to keep
helping you, Mary. To help you find
your home...
92:
You'll meet your family one day, and
you won't have to feel alone
anymore...
95: S-sorry! I just kept blabbering, and—
99:
I'm okay, Will. You're here with me,
aren't you?
103:
I'm always having fun when I'm with
you... All those lonely feelings just
melt away when we're together.
107:
...I feel the same. I always felt so
alone until you came along...
110:
With you at my side, Mary... I couldn't
be happier.
121:
...U-UH! I mean... I'm happy that we're
still good friends after all these
years! Er... Um...
129:
I f-forgot to charge these headsets!
B-battery's about to run out!
140:
Th-that's all for today! Terminate
session "Seaside Valentine"!
144:
If you ever want to visit some other
place, let me know, okay?
A-anyway, gotta go now!
153:
Why?! You HAD him! I don't even
know how someone could mess
that up!
158:
Wahhh... I d-don't know what
happened!
163: I think it's time we called this off.
173:
There's no sense rushing ahead
without knowing why, right?
175:
If she confesses on an impulse, she
might regret it terribly later on.
180:
I, um, well... I don't want to give up, or
anything...
184:
But just look at yourself, Mary. You
were shaking back there.
187:
You're scared, aren't you? The
conditions were all perfect, and yet
you still ran away.
190:
...What are you running from? It
doesn't make sense to make a
move if you don't even know what
direction you're going in.
194:
Th-that's, I... Um, I knew there was a
chance I'd fail, so I...
200:
We can't guarantee you success,
nor can we give you the courage
you need.
202:
More than anything, we can't help
you achieve something you don't
really want.
211:
Let's call things off for now. Once
Mary's calmed down a little—
220:
No! How can you say that? What
part of this don't you understand?!
224:
I'm doing my best, aren't I? I told you
what I want, didn't I?!
228:
I just get scared! I lose my nerve and
freeze up! And I just don't know how
to fix that!
232:
I'm so sick of you talking like you
know everything about me, Reticia!
237:
Very well. We hear you, loud and
clear.
241:
...I...
I'm sorry, forget I said anything...
246:
Why didn't you say so earlier? Now I
know we can do this.
250:
Okay, I gotcha now. You're a real
pain in the butt, aren't you, Mary?
255:
Pain in the what? No, I'm not! I was
just... a little emotional! A-and...
258:
Looks like you finally said what was
on your mind. Keep that up and the
confession will be a cinch.
263:
I'll do my best to help, too. You might
be a pain in the butt, but one I kinda
like.
268:
Hope you're ready, Mary. Let the
meeting for Operation: Snag the
Childhood Friend 2 begin!
